t is required. I’m wondering if I should mention that the daily backup has uncommitted changes, even though the user didn’t specifically ask about it. It’s a bit complex!**Evaluating backup procedures**\n\nI’m considering if a pending backup requires user authorization. That could be something to bring to attention, but earlier heartbeats didn’t mention it, and I should avoid inferring old tasks. I wonder if I need to go through checklists or if I can just rely on context. The instruction in the HEARTBEAT mentions including explanations in checklists, but it seems I don’t necessarily have to read everything. Yet, to execute the scheduled work, I still need to ensure I have the necessary information.**Considering self-improvement tasks**\n\nI need to be cautious about not repeating tasks from previous chats, especially existing anomalies. I can check modification times. If self-improvement is scheduled but hasn't run, I might need to execute it now. I could read the self-improvement checklist to refresh my memory on the commands and rules. It seems good to inspect if any outputs exist; if not, maybe I should run them. I’ll also check the dashboard to see if the state has changed since this morning.**Running self-improvement scripts**\n\nI can run self-improvement scripts, which might generate new outputs. According to the checklist, I need to proactively summarize and report any new file paths created. Since we're in a heartbeat direct channel, I won't respond with \"HEARTBEAT_OK,\" but instead, I'll summarize if new files are generated. If the scripts fail or no new outputs appear, I still need to report something. I'll consider using multi-tool parallel processing to read the self-improvement checklist and check for existing outputs.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OHuy6q4SLB739QlUUJo9yVcA","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/heartbeat-self-improvement.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions